Vol / Page: 89
Edition:
Quote: There is a liking for words in <i>-er</i>, and a whole group of them express admiration: corker, <i>stunner </i> (both used as adjectives as well as nouns)<i>, snitcher </i> (cf. U.S.<i> snitzy), bosker </i>and <i>bonzer </i>: the last was certainly borrowed from Australia.
