Edition:
Quote: A <i> snitch </i> is a grudge or dislike, probably related to the underworld term recorded by Vaux in 1812, <i>to snitch </i> `to betray', and probably unconnected with Australian and New Zealand <i>snitcher </i> `excellent'.
